# Allowlist for Marketplace Token Leak Hunter
#
# Add tokens that should be ignored by the scanner.
# One token per line. Lines starting with # are comments.
#
# Copyright (c) 2025 Rick Deacon / Knostic Labs
#
# USAGE:
# 1. Copy this file to 'allowlist.txt' in your repository root
# 2. Add known false positives (one per line)
# 3. Keep this file in .gitignore if it contains sensitive patterns
#
# WARNING: Only add tokens you are CERTAIN are safe
# - Documentation examples with FAKE prefix
# - Test fixtures with synthetic data
# - Placeholder values in templates
#
# DO NOT add actual rotated production tokens to allowlist

# Example: Documentation tokens with FAKE prefix
ghp_EXAMPLE_TOKEN_FOR_DOCUMENTATION_ONLY
npm_SAMPLE_TOKEN_IN_README_FILE

# Example: Test fixtures
test_fake_token_abc123xyz
TEST_API_KEY_placeholder_12345

# Example: Placeholder values
YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_TOKEN
<YOUR_API_KEY>

# Example: Known safe patterns in templates
$(SECRET_NAME)
${TOKEN_VARIABLE}
